<HEADLINE>
Engine heat, hood vents
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> Lauren...@webtv.net (J J) </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-15T16:30:00 </POSTDATE>
Why do most cars not have any hood vents?   In the summer the temp under
the hood is very high.  (If you want proof, just raise the hood after a
summer trip)

Wouldn't it make more sense to design hood vents into every car?
Wouldn't the entire under hood  area benefit if the max temp was
significantly lower?  I had a Datsun 280Z and it had a hood vent.  It
was designed not to let rain water come in.

Installing one myself would be costly, require some repainting, and
prone to rust.
</POST>
