Under-hood temperatures were a problem when they sealed the cooling
system and went to higher temp thermostats, many years ago.  Many
elastomers were inadequate tor the higher temps.  Fuel lines broke and
there were a rash of engine fires.  Electronics, just coming on board,
failed a lot.

The car mfgrs answer, rather than lower the environment temperature,
was to develop higher temp elastomers and electronics.
